The paper describes a neural network weight compression approach for classification tasks, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision research. The use of a learned probability model and entropy penalty during training suggests a focus on optimization and regularization techniques, which are often studied in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The evaluation on image classification benchmarks also suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the use of compression techniques suggests a focus on data storage and retrieval, which is often studied in the subfield of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
